<br>
Tao translates as &quot;the Way&quot;. It isn't a set of beliefs, but a set of practices, a guideline for how to live a peaceful happy life. It is similar to Buddhism, but different, and not contradictory. A Taoist can be of almost any religion. <br>
<br>
Best book I've ever seen on Taoism was Benjamin Hoff's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The Tao of Pooh</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. And yes, for any of you unfamiliar with it, it explains Taoism from the point of view that Winnie the Pooh is pretty much the perfect Taoist. After that, almost any one of the &quot;miniature&quot; books with translations of Taoist sayings would be very helpful.<br>
<br>
